<subSubSection box="[199,1312,582,607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="220" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,366,715]" box="[199,1312,582,607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,582,607]" pageId="13" pageNumber="220">Etymology.</emphasis>
Named for its similarity to 
<taxonomicName authority="Cook." authorityName="Cook." box="[644,828,582,607]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Dropursa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[644,752,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="220">Dropursa</emphasis>
Cook.
</taxonomicName>
The gender of the new genus is masculine.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="220" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1436,366,715]" pageId="13" pageNumber="220">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,618,643]" pageId="13" pageNumber="220">Remarks.</emphasis>
In almost all characters the new genus is similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[892,1000,619,642]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Dropursa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[892,1000,619,642]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="220">Dropursa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the unusual modification of both the first and second leg warrants a separate generic status. Besides the difference in the modified second leg, other differences are found in the closely located heavy setae of PIV; in 
<taxonomicName box="[957,1065,691,714]" class="Arachnida" family="Hygrobatidae" genus="Dropursa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="13" pageNumber="220" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[957,1065,691,714]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="220">Dropursa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
these setae are well separated.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
